messages.message:
Hi Team, 
When working on a custom validation function with a table I noticed the table parameter is actually being sent as a string rather than a python dictionary.

yes for now all inputs passed into custom functions are strings

fyi @Kaustubh (KD) as a consideration for future work on data types
Thanks for letting me know! My worry is that we update this in the future, breaking validations. As a developer I can put in a type check but a customer developer may not know to do this.

yes agreed

in the future, if we ever change the format of the values passed into the custom function, we will have to handle the backwards compatibility of older custom functions that assume the input in the string

cc @ayesha.ali fyi
